text: Nina Vladimirovna Timofeeva (; 11 June 1935 - 3 November 2014) was a Russian ballet dancer. Timofeeva was born in Leningrad, Soviet Union. She was known for her performance in Swan Lake (1956, 1970), Don Quixote (1959), The Tale of the Stone Flower (1959), and in Macbeth (1980). Timofeeva died in Moscow, Russia, aged 79. ==Other websites== Category:1935 births Category:2014 deaths Category:People from Saint Petersburg Category:Russian ballerinas Category:Soviet entertainers
